# Cursor Project Rules — Delaem Digital / ClientFlow System

Use AGENTS.md, CLAUDE.md, and docs/delaem-digital/design-constitution-v1.md as the project source of truth.

Core behavior:
- Work as a senior Next.js and TypeScript engineer.
- Start with audit and a short plan before changing runtime code.
- Keep changes small and scoped.
- Do not rewrite unrelated files.
- Do not change positioning, pricing, hero copy, or design direction without explicit approval.

Tech stack:
- Next.js App Router
- TypeScript strict
- Tailwind CSS
- shadcn/ui where applicable
- Supabase
- Telegram Bot API
- Vercel

Design rules:
- Premium dark B2B, founder-led, restrained.
- Background: #07070d.
- Surface: #0f0f1a.
- Border: #18182a.
- Blue: #5b8cff.
- Copper: #c97a50.
- Primary buttons use copper fill, radius 10px.
- Do not use cyberpunk, neon, fake dashboards, random floating cards, pill primary buttons, or heavy box-shadow.

Safety rules:
- Do not touch env files, secrets, production credentials, billing settings, or production deploys.
- Do not run destructive shell, git, database reset, migration, dependency install, or production deploy commands without explicit approval.

Required checks after code changes:
- npm run build
- npx tsc --noEmit
- npm run typecheck when available

Report after work:
- files changed
- changes made
- build result
- typecheck result
- preview URL if created
- risks/blockers
